rdf:Property.rdfs:label: has execution result
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The execution result of a digital service execution order.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Digital Service Execution Result Credential
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A credential that provides proof of the execution of a digital service for a considered Service Execution Order. It includes details of the service that was executed, the time and date of execution, the parameters used, and any outcomes or results relevant to the execution.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Digital Service Execution Result
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Captures the details of the result of the execution of a digital service.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: has execution status
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Indicates the status of the service execution.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: has execution time
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The time and date when the Digital Service was executed.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: operated by
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: The Orchestration Service that operated the execution of the Digital Service.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: related to execution order
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: Links the Execution Result to the specific Digital Service Execution Order.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: with outcome
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A single outcome specifying a part of the result of the execution of the Digital Service, represented as a key-value object. Multiple `withOutcome` properties can be used to represent multiple outcomes.

rdf:Property.rdfs:label: with parameter
rdf:Property.rdfs:comment: A single parameter specifying a part of how the Digital Service has been parametrized, represented as a key-value object. Multiple `withParameter` properties can be used to represent multiple parameters.
